{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"569f7d93-52ca-45a4-9dd3-6d6b15ec7ba7","content":"Your `.testsettings` file is a legacy format no longer supported by modern MSTest. You need to migrate it to a `.runsettings` file. Here's what your settings map to:\n\n| `.testsettings` setting | `.runsettings` equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `TestTimeout = 30000` | `<MSTest><TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>` |\n| Code Coverage DataCollector | `<DataCollectors>` section |\n| `AssemblyResolution / useLoadContext` | Not needed (modern MSTest handles this) |","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01M6GTgbFcwh6gdEP1pAnUBH","name":"create","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-7470ad0ab9d14c72a647da7caf877ec4/local.runsettings","file_text":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>\n  </MSTest>\n  <DataCollectionRunSettings>\n    <DataCollectors>\n      <DataCollector friendlyName=\"Code Coverage\"\n        uri=\"datacollector://Microsoft/CodeCoverage/2.0\"\n        assemblyQualifiedName=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector.SingleFileDataCollector, Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector, Culture=neutral\">\n        <Configuration>\n          <CodeCoverage />\n        </Configuration>\n      </DataCollector>\n    </DataCollectors>\n  </DataCollectionRunSettings>\n</RunSettings>\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"create a new file at /tmp/sv-7470ad0ab9d14c72a647da7caf877ec4/local.runsettings."}],"interactionId":"cf478f0d-b92a-4232-a83f-73b19a69a889","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a `.testsettings` file that's being ignored after upgrading to MSTest 3.x. The `.testsettings` format is legacy (Visual Studio 2010 era) and modern MSTest uses `.runsettings` instead. I need to help them migrate.\n\nLet me create an equivalent `.runsettings` file and update the `.csproj` to reference it.\n\nThe `.testsettings` has:\n1. Assembly resolution with `useLoadContext=\"true\"` — not needed in modern MSTest\n2. `TestTimeout` of 30000ms — maps to `<TestTimeout>` in `<MSTest>` section of `.runsettings`\n\n\n3. Code coverage data collector — maps to `<DataCollectors>` in `.runsettings`\n\nNow I'll build out the `.runsettings` file with these settings.","outputTokens":626,"requestId":"7C10:9F1F0:1768A21:1A94839:69F95952"},"id":"a2d5a2b9-b96c-4fbf-b204-4b869af4838f","timestamp":"2026-05-05T02:43:41.431Z","parentId":"175e43fe-c755-4a3a-ad35-18248bff39d2"}
